PhosR: stably phosphorylated sites(SPS) identification and integration of liver time-course datasets

Di Xiao; Pengyi Yang

04 April, 2020

Description: This Rmarkdown file documents (1) the identification of stably phosphorylated sites(SPS) from four phosphoproteomic datasets; and (2) the integration the two time-course datasets from liver phosphoproteome upon insulin stimulation.

library(PhosR)
## Registered S3 methods overwritten by 'ggplot2':
##   method         from 
##   [.quosures     rlang
##   c.quosures     rlang
##   print.quosures rlang
library(directPA)
setwd("./")

# identification datasets
# phosphoproteomic dataset from time-course mouse embryonic stem cell differentiation
load("phospho_ESC_ratio.RData") # label free
# phosphoproteomic dataset of controls and FGF21 treated mouse 3T3-L1 adipocytes
load("phospho_L1_FGF21_ratio_v2.RData") # SILCA
# phosphoproteomic dataset of controls and insulin stimulated, and LY or MK inhibited mouse 3T3-L1 adipocytes
load("phospho_L1_Ins_ratio.RData") # L1 Ins SILCA
# phosphoproteomic dataset of insulin stimulation of FL83B and Hepa1-6
load("phospho_NB_cells_Ins_ratios.RData") # Sean NB, cell lines Ins

1 step 1: find overlaps in identification datasets

ESC.Diff.sites <- gsub("~[STY]", "~", sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.ESC.ratio), "~"), 
                                             function(x){paste(toupper(x[2]), x[3], sep="~")}))

L1.FGF21.sites <- gsub("~[STY]", "~", sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio), "~"), 
                                             function(x){paste(toupper(x[2]), x[3], sep="~")}))

L1.Ins.sites <- sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.L1.Ins.ratio), ";"), function(x){paste(x[1], x[2], sep="~")})

NB.cells.sites <- gsub("~[STY]", "~", sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.NB.cells.Ins.ratios), "~"), 
                                             function(x){paste(toupper(x[2]), x[3], sep="~")}))
# calculate the mean of replicates 
tmp <- do.call(cbind, lapply(split(1:ncol(phospho.ESC.ratio), gsub("_\\d+", "", colnames(phospho.ESC.ratio))), 
              function(i){rowMeans(phospho.ESC.ratio[,i])}))
phospho.ESC.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(tmp), ESC.Diff.sites), colMeans))[,-1]

tmp <- do.call(cbind, lapply(split(1:ncol(phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio), gsub("FGF_r\\d.", "", 
              colnames(phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio))), function(i){rowMeans(phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio[,i])}))
phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(tmp), L1.FGF21.sites), colMeans))

tmp <- do.call(cbind, lapply(split(1:ncol(phospho.NB.cells.Ins.ratios), gsub("_\\d+", "",  
              colnames(phospho.NB.cells.Ins.ratios))),function(i){rowMeans(phospho.NB.cells.Ins.ratios[,i])}))
phospho.Multi.Ins.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(tmp), NB.cells.sites), colMeans))[,-c(1,3)]

phospho.L1.Ins.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(phospho.L1.Ins.ratio), L1.Ins.sites), colMeans))
# maximum fold change for each phosphosite
phospho.L1.FGF21.max <- apply(phospho.L1.FGF21.ratio.sites, 1, function(x){x[which.max(abs(x))]})
phospho.ESC.Diff.max <- apply(phospho.ESC.ratio.sites, 1, function(x){x[which.max(abs(x))]})
phospho.L1.Ins.max <- apply(phospho.L1.Ins.ratio.sites, 1, function(x){x[which.max(abs(x))]})
phospho.Multi.Ins.max <- apply(phospho.Multi.Ins.ratio.sites, 1, function(x){x[which.max(abs(x))]})

# find overlaps in four datasets with maximum fold change
o <- mIntersect(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites)
Ts <- cbind(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[o], phospho.ESC.Diff.max[o], phospho.L1.Ins.max[o], phospho.Multi.Ins.max[o])

2 step 2: rank by fold changes

# rank phosphosites by absolute fold change
Tc <- (apply(-abs(Ts),2,rank)-0.5)/nrow(Ts)

# four-way overlappling
Tt4 <- pchisq(-2*rowSums(log(Tc)),6,lower.tail = FALSE)
index = names(which(Tt4>0.95))
pairs(Ts, col = rownames(Ts)%in%index+1)

HC = rainbow(length(Tt4) * 1.2)
pairs(Ts, col = HC[rank(-Tt4)])

sites.sorted <- names(sort(Tt4, decreasing=TRUE))

# Boxplots of absolute fold changes in phosphorylation of four datasets. Phosphosites are grouped into five categories including those that are unique to each of the four phosphoproteomic datasets and 1027 overlapped phosphosites.
par(mfrow=c(1,4))
boxplot(abs(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[!(names(phospho.L1.FGF21.max) %in% mUnion(ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites,NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[Reduce(intersect, list(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[(names(phospho.L1.FGF21.max) %in% sites.sorted[1:100])]),
        abs(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[(names(phospho.L1.FGF21.max) %in% sites.sorted[501:600])]),
        abs(phospho.L1.FGF21.max[(names(phospho.L1.FGF21.max) %in% sites.sorted[1001:1100])]),notch=TRUE, outline = FALSE, 
        col=c("grey", "orange", "blue", "purple", "red"), ylab="log2 FC", main="L1 FGF21")

boxplot(abs(phospho.ESC.Diff.max[!(names(phospho.ESC.Diff.max) %in% mUnion(L1.FGF21.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.ESC.Diff.max[Reduce(intersect, list(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.ESC.Diff.max[(names(phospho.ESC.Diff.max) %in% sites.sorted[1:100])]),
        abs(phospho.ESC.Diff.max[(names(phospho.ESC.Diff.max) %in% sites.sorted[501:600])]),
        abs(phospho.ESC.Diff.max[(names(phospho.ESC.Diff.max) %in% sites.sorted[1001:1100])]),notch=TRUE, outline = FALSE, 
        col=c("grey", "orange", "blue", "purple", "red"), ylab="log2 FC", main="ESC Diff")

boxplot(abs(phospho.L1.Ins.max[!(names(phospho.L1.Ins.max) %in% mUnion(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.L1.Ins.max[Reduce(intersect, list(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.L1.Ins.max[(names(phospho.L1.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[1:100])]),
        abs(phospho.L1.Ins.max[(names(phospho.L1.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[501:600])]),
        abs(phospho.L1.Ins.max[(names(phospho.L1.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[1001:1100])]),notch=TRUE, outline = FALSE, 
        col=c("grey", "orange", "blue", "purple", "red"), ylab="log2 FC", main="L1 Ins, LY, & MK")

boxplot(abs(phospho.Multi.Ins.max[!(names(phospho.Multi.Ins.max) %in% mUnion(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.Multi.Ins.max[Reduce(intersect, list(L1.FGF21.sites, ESC.Diff.sites, L1.Ins.sites, NB.cells.sites))]),
        abs(phospho.Multi.Ins.max[(names(phospho.Multi.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[1:100])]),
        abs(phospho.Multi.Ins.max[(names(phospho.Multi.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[501:600])]),
        abs(phospho.Multi.Ins.max[(names(phospho.Multi.Ins.max) %in% sites.sorted[1001:1100])]),notch=TRUE, outline = FALSE,
        col=c("grey", "orange", "blue", "purple", "red"), ylab="log2 FC", main="FL83B and Hepa 1-6 Ins")

### test dataset 2 normalise Insulin diff data
## NB liver Ins TC
load("phospho_mice_liver_Ins_TC_ratio_test.RData")
dim(phospho.mice.liver.Ins.TC.ratio)
## [1] 9687   90
liver.Ins.TC.sites <- gsub("~[STY]", "~", sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.mice.liver.Ins.TC.ratio), "~"), function(x){paste(toupper(x[2]), x[3], sep="~")}))
phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(phospho.mice.liver.Ins.TC.ratio), liver.Ins.TC.sites), colMeans))

f <- paste("X_", sapply(strsplit(colnames(phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites), "_"), function(x){x[3]}), sep="")
design <- model.matrix(~ f - 1)


set.seed(1)
phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.RUV <- RUVphospho(phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites, M=design, k=4, ctl=which(rownames(phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites) %in% sites.sorted[1:100]))

# check results
cs <- rainbow(length(unique(f)))
colorCodes <- sapply(f, switch, X_0s=cs[1], X_5s=cs[2], X_10s=cs[3], X_15s=cs[4], X_30s=cs[5], X_1m=cs[6],
                     X_2m=cs[7], X_3m=cs[8], X_4m=cs[9], X_6m=cs[10], X_10m=cs[11])

par(mfrow=c(2,1))
tmp <- phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites
colnames(tmp) <- gsub("Intensity.Liver_Ins_", "", colnames(tmp))
h1 <- hclust(dist(t(tmp)))
plotQC(tmp, panel=2, cols = colorCodes, main="Before normalisation")
mclust::adjustedRandIndex(cutree(h1, k = 11), f)
## [1] 0.5052129
tmp <- phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.RUV
colnames(tmp) <- gsub("Intensity.Liver_Ins_", "", colnames(tmp))
h2 <- hclust(dist(t(tmp)))
plotQC(tmp, panel=2, cols = colorCodes, main="After normalisation")

mclust::adjustedRandIndex(cutree(h2, k = 11), f)
## [1] 0.8639863
# AKT1~309
library(ggplot2)
x <- sapply(f, switch, X_0s=1, X_5s=2, X_10s=3, X_15s=4, X_30s=5, X_1m=6, X_2m=7, X_3m=8, X_4m=9, X_6m=10, X_10m=11)
df <- data.frame("y"=phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.sites["AKT1~309",], "x"=x)
ggplot(df, aes(x = x, y = y)) + geom_point(color=colorCodes, size=2) + theme_classic() + geom_smooth(method = 'loess', span = 0.9) + ggtitle("AKT1 309; Before normalisation") + xlab("Time") + ylab("log2 FC")

df <- data.frame(y=phospho.liver.Ins.TC.ratio.RUV["AKT1~309",], x=x)
ggplot(df, aes(x = x, y = y)) + geom_point(color=colorCodes, size=2) + theme_classic() + geom_smooth(method = 'loess', span = 0.9) + ggtitle("AKT1 309; RUV normalised") + xlab("Time") + ylab("log2 FC")
